<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Marcelo Bielsa has confirmed that he will stay on as Leeds United manager next season.</p>

<p>The Argentine was out of contract this summer and, while the club were always confident he would commit to a new deal, no news had been forthcoming.</p>

<p>But, speaking on Thursday ahead of Saturday's trip to Liverpool, Bielsa said: 'I will be working the next season at Leeds United. Everything has been sorted and I'll definitely be here next season.'</p>

<p>More to follow...</p>

<p>Marcelo Bielsa will stay at Leeds United after his contract was due to expire in the summer</p>
